Lake Level 1.46; good for this time of year; sunny- west wind- choppy- suspended green particles- floating weeds from people doing water sports in the shallow water
Water level 1.36; good level for August; partly cloudy- NE wind- choppy
Sunny- southwest wind- choppy- hot and humid- high 90- floating weed from boating activity
Water Level 1.52; over 3 inches of rain this past week- colder than normal last two days- high in 50s and lows in 40s; very windy past two days; cloudy- NW wind

Ice out April 2; Calibrated D.O. sensor; SE wind- cloudy- rain/snow mix in the forecast this week; Buffalo head duck on the lake; loon flying overhead; 1.60 lake level; normal level for spring; SE wind- cloudy- rain/snow mix in the forecast this week; Buffalo head duck on the lake; loon flying overhead

Haze- smoke from Alberta's wildfire- has been very windy lately- shoreline erosion with the high water level and winds- yesterday's high was in the 90s and today is cooler in the low 60s- rained 1/4" last night with thunderstorms in the area- east wind
Sunny- calm- beautiful spring day- floating insect casings and cottonwood seeds; Cisco jumping to surface feed

Rained over 2 inches this week- beautiful Memorial Day- sunny- clear skies- NW wind- floating insect casings and pine needles- decomposition foam- eroding shoreline due to high water and waves crashing on shore
Lake level is high for summer; 1.58; someone lost a dock section; sunny- NW wind- yesterday floating green scum from lake bottom; shoreline weeds are surrounded by scum
Sunny- SE breeze- gusty north wind the past week- beautiful summer morning- 2 loons

Lake level is still high for this time of year. 1.60 in. Storm moved through the area last Saturday with 60 mph winds. Trees were snapped on the west shore of Sand Lake along Hwy 70; we received over 3 in of rain. Today is a beautiful summer day- sunny with scattered clouds.

Lake level 1.69; high for July; mostly cloudy- calm; approximately 2.5" of rain on July 11; flooding in Hayward and other parts NW Wisconsin; shoreline erosion Lake level 1.69; high for July; mostly cloudy- calm; approximately 2.5" of rain on July 11; flooding in Hayward and other parts NW Wisconsin; shoreline erosion; 2 loons Staff gauge 1.69 ft; high for July; mostly cloudy- calm; approximately 2.5" of rain on July 11; flooding in Hayward and other parts NW Wisconsin; shoreline erosion; 2 loons

Lake Level 1.57 ft; high for July; clear skies- light west wind- lot of watercraft activity; shoreline erosion from the waves crashing on shore; suspended green algae; floating clumps of weeds most likely from boaters; hot in the 90s today and yesterday and tropical dew points; very humid
Lake level 1.34 ft; still high for this time of year; Partly cloudy; light westerly breeze- suspended algae particles; rained approximately 3 inches the past two weeks.
Lake level 1.37 ft; nice level for this time of year-west wind- 1 in of rain the last two days
Lake level 1.29; a good lake level but high for the end of August; light rain yesterday; partly cloudy-light wind
Lake level 1.28 ft; good for late summer; beautiful September morning; rained this week over 1 in.; sunny; southwesterly wind; yesterday gusty northerly wind; forecast is for gusty winds later today
Water level is high for fall at 1.51 in. On Thursday- Sept 22- we had 3 inches of rain; 3 loons changing colors; cloudy
Ice on Dec 17- 2016; ice off April 7; 1.48 lake level which is low for early spring; cloudy NE wind- air temp 44 deg F; we have had a lot of windy days and days with gusty winds
Lake level 1.46 which is low for spring; sunny- clear skies. easterly wind
Water level 1.78 normal spring level; rained last night- cloudy
Lake level 1.89 normal spring level; rained approximately 1" last night- floating insect casing and shoreline debris- sunny- west wind

1.92 lake level; high water level for this time of year; rainy and windy weather; big storm with high winds and over 3" of rain moved through on Sunday- June 11 - trees fell on structures- downbursts caused large amount of uprooted and snapped trees- power outages; mostly cloudy- light NW breeze- 2 young loons with an adult loon in Moe's Bay
1.79 lake level; high for this time of year but a good level; weather has been on and off showers; windy- sunny- cirrus clouds- suspended particles- westerly breeze- few Cisco jumping in the evening
1.60 lake level; good summer level but higher than normal for July; sunny- ripples- suspended particles; beautiful fourth of July week; a lot of people on the lake
1.44 lake level; nice summer level but higher than normal; sunny- NE breeze- 2 adult loons with 2 baby loons
1.38 lake level; good summer level; sunny- light southerly wind- suspended particles
1.28 lake level; sunny- beautiful day; suspended particles
1.21 lake level; sunny with cirrostratus clouds; calm; 2 loons; suspended particles
1.13 water level- sunny- clear skies- light ENE wind- suspended particles- 1 loon- nice morning
1.41 lake level- rained approximately 3.5 inches last Saturday- partly cloudy- NE wind- choppy- one loon
1.40 lake level- overcast- cooler air temperatures than normal the past few days- calm- drizzly day- jumping cisco- 2 loons "dancing"
1.32 lake level- clear skies- calm- beautiful day-high temperature in the  70s or low 80s the past few days- a few trees are changing color- cisco jumping- 2 loons
1.24 lake level- gloomy day- overcast- light SW wind- loon changing colors

1.23 lake level- mostly sunny-light westerly breeze- decomposition foam on the NE shore and foam floating on the lake- 2 loons with fall color change- a few trees are just starting to change color- warm September- last weekend highs in middle 80s and very humid- 50 deg F air temperature at 9 am
1.35 lake level; has been cloudy with drizzle or rain and windy- overcast- very light westerly breeze (about 5mph)-2 loons- more leaves are changing color the last couple of days

Water level 1.45"; very light rain last night- sunny- thin layer of clouds- calm; tiny insect casings floating (fish flies); Hot Memorial Day weekend with highs in upper 80s and low 90s. La Nina year so was brutally cold
Heavy rain weekend of 6/15-17/18.  Over 5" of rain.
Lake dropped over a foot due to prolonged dry conditions.
More rain recently.  Lake level is slightly higher- but still low.
Lake level is high from a rainy Spring. Dave Ruzicka assisting in monitoring activities.  Battery level low on Temp./DO meter.
SSE Wind blowing at 15+ mph.  Difficult to read Secchi depth.  Returned on 7/27/2019 for Secchi reading. Dave Ruzicka assisted with lake monitoring.  New batteries in Temp./DO meter.

Beautiful morning in the 60s with a light northerly breeze.  Dave Ruzicka assisted with the lake monitoring.  Lake level is down approximately 1.5 feet from June level.  Lake level is normal for this time of year.

Blue sky with a light breeze and no clouds.  Very dry conditions.  Lake level is high from the Spring melt.  Lake is clear with no suspended particles and light to moderate staining from drainage during the melt.
Overcast and breezy with SE wind with small waves and temperature in mid 70s.
Lake Level low due to dry conditions.  Sunny calm day in upper 70s.  Water slightly tinted green from suspended particles.
69 degrees with SE Breeze at 10 mph.  Blue sky with clouds.
